    <div class="alpheios-lex-entry" lemma-id="n7911" body-key="α">
          <b><span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">πότνια</span></b> , voc. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">πότνα</span> (cf. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">πόσις 2,
            δέσποινα</span>): <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">mistress, queen</span>, <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">θηρῶν</span>, Artemis, <i><span class="en">Il.
            21.470</span></i>; freq. as honorable title or epith. of goddesses and
          women, <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">πότνα θεά̄</span>, ‘mighty’ goddess
          (cf. ‘our Lady’), <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">πότνια μήτηρ</span>,
          ‘revered,’ ‘honored,’ <i><span class="en">Od.
          18.5</span></i>.</div> <div class="alpheios-lex-footnotes en"> </div>
